President Donald J. Trump will be hosting the President of the Republic of Palau, the President of the Republic of the Marshall Islands, and the President of the Federated States of Micronesia at the White House on May 21, 2019. This will be the first time that all three leaders of the Freely Associated States (FAS) are hosted together by a United States president. The meeting aims to discuss the strong security ties between the United States and the FAS, their shared commitment to democracy and the rule of law, and their mutual interest in maintaining a free and open Pacific.